  • 2012-01-26 00:33:37

    Re: Videos get stuck when I try to pause them

    No, that's not quite our issue. There isn't any degradation near the end or other ill effects when near the end of the video. Pause/Play works fine, but if you try to navigate away from the page, nothing happens- the status bar reports 'transferring data' ...

    This happens on FF 9 Windows ; IE 9 ; FF 3.5 for Mac.

    It appears that the request for the next page is queued up behind the video file download- the browser goes to a link clicked on while the video file is downloading, after the video file has finished.

    This might actually be a desirable feature in some class settings- forcing the student to at least wait as long as the file takes to download, though not be viewed, before the student can navigate on.

    But for our purposes- we have some big video files- it would make more sense for the viewer to navigate between the the pages when a video is still in midflight.

    Safari does not have this issue- it allows the user to navigate away from a page whether the video is playing, paused, or still downloading.
    Does anyone know how to tweak flowplayer to get the other browsers to behave more Safari-esque?


  • 2012-01-26 11:32:37

    Re: Videos get stuck when I try to pause them

    That link is actually there as a backup if the player does not load. You can click the links to open the video in a local media player.

    If you want to remove it you can edit it out of:
    /mods/_standard/flowplayer/module_format_content.php

    Around lines 31 to 39.
